  "body": "I have contract with bool in constructor parameters:\r\nconstructor(\r\n  address p1,\r\n  address p2,\r\n  bool p3\r\n)\r\nSame contract deployed with p3 true for first and p3 false for second\r\nFirst one with p3 true is verifying fine\r\nSecond with p3 false not\r\nAfter quick researches I figured out that third parameter \"false\" always parsing as true and gives 1 in encoded parameters\r\nI tried:\r\nnpx hardhat verify --network opera 0xd9...3F6 \"0x3A...62\" \"0x86...83\" \"false\"\r\nnpx hardhat verify --network opera 0xd9...3F6 \"0x3A...62\" \"0x86...83\" false\r\nnpx hardhat verify --network opera 0xd9...3F6 \"0x3A...62\" \"0x86...83\" \"0\"\r\nnpx hardhat verify --network opera 0xd9...3F6 \"0x3A...62\" \"0x86...83\" 0\r\nAll gives ...1 instead ...0 in parameters\r\nHowever when I'm using --constructor-args with separate file for parameters it works like expected.",
